Package: SDMconnectR
Title: Simple Tools for Species Distribution Modeling and Connectivity
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Jolien", "Grafe", , "jolien.grafe@stud-mail.wuerzburg-uni.de", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A minimal and modular toolkit for fitting species distribution models (SDMs) 
    and analyzing landscape connectivity. The package provides functions for 
    generating pseudo-absence points, fitting GLM-based SDMs, projecting models 
    onto environmental raster layers, converting suitability to resistance, 
    computing least-cost paths between points, and evaluating model performance 
    with AUC and confusion matrices.
Imports: 
    terra (>= 1.7),
    sf (>= 1.0),
    leastcostpath (>= 0.4),
    pROC (>= 1.18),
    stats
